The police have arrested two suspected burglars in Abaji with items worth N400,000 allegedly stolen from a shop belonging to the wife of the Ona of Abaji, Alhaji Adamu Baba Yunusa. A resident, Aliyu Musa, said police officers arrested the suspects yesterday with the items, but that the shop, on Sokodabo Street, was burgled on Friday. Musa said the suspects broke into the shop and stole children’s wares. “One of the sales girls discovered that the shop was burgled and baby items worth N400,000 were carted away,” he said. He said the wife of the traditional ruler reported at the police station when she learnt about the incident. The Abaji Divisional Police Officer (DPO) CSP Tersoo Tile, confirmed the incident. “Two suspects have been arrested in connection with the burgling of the shop. Investigation is ongoing,” he said.